commit.message:
Fix get_kernel_workgroup_info for Intel

We can not query the returned size as in the other info groups
for get_kernel_workgroup_info on Intel.
(see: https://github.com/CNugteren/CLTune/issues/43)

Instead add a default size field in ecl_info_t and use
def_size instead of doing a query if def_size > 0.

Makefile win32 fixes

Define WIN_X64 for 64b builds with mingw-gcc.

Detection of cl.exe did not work so you had to force
using gcc on mingw.

Reorder stuff and support WSLcross build if defined.

Add calling convention to (dll) functions

OpenCL uses the non default __stdcall on Windows.

Thus function types for dynamicly loaded functions must specify
calling convention otherwise the stack gets trashed.

Fix warnings on win32
removed warnings
dynamic load of all openCL functions, this makes it easier to patch variants and implement backwards compatible code
